}}

The '''A801''' is a road in [[Scotland]] which runs from east of [[Polmont]] to the [[A705 road|A705]] near [[Whitburn, West Lothian|Whitburn]] that heads towards [[Livingston, West Lothian|Livingston]] in the other direction.

{{GeoGroupTemplate}}
{{coord|55.9298|-3.6789|dim:10000_region:GB|display=title|name=A801 road}}

The '''A801 '''provides a link from the [[M8 motorway (Scotland)|M8]] to the [[M9 motorway (Scotland)|M9]], creating easy access from travellers from Falkirk or Stirling to places in West Lothian like Livingston. 
{{GB A road zone 8}}

{{DEFAULTSORT:8-0801}}
