{{Refimprove|date=February 2017}}
[[File:Adyanpara Waterfalls During Rainy Season.png|thumb|Adyanpara Waterfalls during the rainy season|alt=]]
'''Adyanpara Falls''' is a cascading [[waterfall]] in the Kurmbalangodu village of [[Nilambur]] taluk in [[Kerala]], [[India]]. It is {{Convert|14|km|mi}} from [[Nilambur]] town, and attracts tourists from various parts of Kerala.{{fact|date=May 2018}} This is a seasonal waterfall. During Summer, water flow is low.<ref>[http://nilambur-attractions.blogspot.in/2015/07/adyanpara-waterfalls.html Adyanpara Waterfalls Nilambur, A day worth visiting]</ref> This waterfall is of a natural cascading style as the waterfall descends over the rock.<ref>{{Citation|last=Malayalam Talk|title=Adyanpara Waterfalls During Rainy Season Near Nilambur Malappuram Kerala Tourism|date=2017-07-21|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lyAa2obZVNs|accessdate=2017-07-23}}</ref>

