{{short description|A seamount named in honor of the Russian scientist, Valeri Barsukov}}
'''Barsukov Seamount''' ({{Coord|61|3|S|29|12|W|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a [[seamount]] named in honor of the Russian scientist, [[Valeri Barsukov]]<!-- sic. source incorrectly gives B as the initial for the Cyrillic letter В, usually transliterated as V -->, former Director of the [[Vernadsky Institute of Geochemistry]]. The name proposed by Dr. [[G.B. Udintsev]], of the same institute, and approved by the [[Advisory Committee for Undersea Features]] in June 1995.

