{{short description|One of the New England Seamounts in the North Atlantic}} {{Infobox Seamount | Name=Manning Seamount | Photo= | Photo caption= | Height= | Location= North [[Atlantic Ocean]] | Map = [[Image:NE seamounts.jpg|300px|]] | Country = | Coordinates ={{Coord|38|9|54.5|N|60|40|0|W|display=inline,title}} | Type=[[Guyot]] | Volcanic group = [[New England Seamounts]] | Age= | Last eruption= }}
The '''Manning Seamount''' is a [[guyot]] in the [[Atlantic Ocean]]. It is part of the [[New England Seamounts]], which was active more than 100 million years ago. It was formed when the [[North American Plate]] moved over the [[New England hotspot]].<ref name="NOAA2">{{cite web | title = Geological Origin of the New England Seamount Chain | work = National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration | publisher = U.S. Department of Commerce | year = 2005 | url = http://www.oceanexplorer.noaa.gov/explorations/03mountains/background/geology/geology.html | accessdate = 2007-09-16 }}</ref>
