'''Rio Xufexufe''' is a river in the [[São Tomé Island|island of São Tomé]], [[São Tomé and Príncipe]]. The river flows southward through the southern part of the [[Lembá District]] and empties into the [[Atlantic Ocean]] 10 km northwest of [[Vila Malanza]]. Its catchment area is {{convert|16.5|km2|abbr=on}}.<ref>[http://www.aler-renovaveis.org/contents/activitieseventsspeakersdocuments/belizardo-neto_recursos-e-projectos-er_dgrne_8716.pdf Recursos e Projectos de Energias Renováveis], Associação Lusófona de Energias Renováveis, p. 6</ref> The endangered birds [[São Tomé olive pigeon]] (''Columba thomensis'')<ref name=iucn>{{cite journal|url=https://www.iucnredlist.org/species/22690138/93262041|page=e.T22690138A93262041|title=''Columba thomensis'' |author=BirdLife International |author-link=BirdLife International |year=2016 |journal=[[The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species]]|accessdate=1 November 2018|doi= 10.2305/IUCN.UK.2016-3.RLTS.T22690138A93262041.en}}</ref> and [[São Tomé fiscal]] (''Lanius newtoni'') have been observed in the catchment of the river.<ref name=iucn2>{{cite journal|url=https://www.iucnredlist.org/species/22705080/111021834|page=e.T22705080A111021834|title=''Lanius newtoni'' |author=BirdLife International |author-link=BirdLife International |year=2017 |journal=[[The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species]]|accessdate=26 October 2018|doi= 10.2305/IUCN.UK.2017-1.RLTS.T22705080A111021834.en}}</ref>

